Definition.WordDefinition: Visa \Vi"sa\, v. t. [imp. & p. p. {Visaed}; p. pr. & vb. n. {Visaing}.] To indorse, after examination, with the word vis['e], as a passport; to vis['e]. [1913 Webster]
visa n : an endorsement made in a passport that allows the bearer to enter the country issuing it v 1: provide (a passport) with a visa 2: approve officially; "The list of speakers must be visaed"
